Title : The Miracle at Cardenrigg
Text : {{italic title}}
'''''The Miracle at Cardenrigg''''' is a novel by the Scottish writer [[Tom Hanlin]] published by Random House in 1949.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hanlin|first1=Tom|title=Miracle at Cardenrigg: A Novel|publisher=Random House|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Miracle_at_Cardenrigg.html?id=2VQ_AQAAIAAJ|language=en}}</ref>

==Plot==
Two hundred miners are trapped underground.  The story of their survival involves both adventure and suspense.<ref name="kirkus">{{cite web|title=THE MIRACLE AT CARDENRIGG by Tom Hanlin|url=https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/tom-hanlin/the-miracle-at-cardenrigg/|website=www.kirkusreviews|accessdate=July 18, 2016|language=en-us}}</ref>

